<br>
Let me use your own numbers here for a minute. 420,000 paying customers. Lets take an average time when there are, say, 200,000 people connected and playing (during peak times, maybe). On average, each of these accounts will be both sending/recieving data at approximately 5kb/sec.<br>
200,000 * 5kb/sec = 1,000,000kb/sec<br>
= 976gb/sec<br>
= Almost a terabyte a second. A @#%$ <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> terabyte</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Thats quite a lot of motherfucking data. Do you think its free to have 1400 computers transferring terabytes upon terabytes of data at any given time? Er. No. A game like this is VERY expensive to run and the pricing is reasonable. Prices will soon be $13.95 or something a month, correct? How much is a movie where you live? It's about $6.50 here. Now, seeing as the average movie is about 2 hours long, for the same price as a month of EverQuest, I can get 4 hours of entertainment at a movie theater. Considering most people play 30 to 100+ hours of EQ a month, thats a pretty good @#%$ deal.<br>
<br>
Honestly, what do you expect? It to be free? For them to pay you to play? This is a business and they are in it to make money, not to make friends. In all seriousness, if you don't like it, you may get all of your friend's email addresses, sell your account, and keep in touch with them that way for free. Really. If you don't like the game, quit. They release expansions as they see fit, and if you do not agree with this, I welcome you to start your own software company to spite them.<br>
